{:spec/title "Wire runtime spec network-policy and secrets to Docker executor"

 :spec/description
 "Per N11 §5.1, the runtime specification declares :network-policy and :secrets
  that should be applied to the capsule. Currently these fields exist in the
  spec but are not read by the runner or passed to the Docker executor.

  Implementation:
  1. In runner.clj acquire-execution-environment!, read :runtime-spec from
     the workflow opts or workflow config. Pass it to the executor's
     acquire-environment! as part of env-config.
  2. In docker.clj acquire-environment!, read :network-policy from env-config:
     - :deny-all (default) → --network=none (already implemented)
     - :allow [{:host \"api.anthropic.com\" :port 443}...] → build iptables
       rules or use a custom Docker network with allowed endpoints
     - For initial implementation, support :deny-all and :allow-all only.
       Per-endpoint allow-listing is deferred to a follow-up.
  3. In docker.clj acquire-environment!, read :secrets from env-config:
     - Each secret has {:name :scope :source}
     - :scope :env → inject as -e NAME=VALUE on container create
     - :scope :file → write to capsule filesystem during bootstrap
     - :source :env → read from host environment
     - :source :config → read from user profile config
  4. Never log secret values. Log secret names only."

 :spec/intent {:type :feature
               :scope ["components/workflow/src/ai/miniforge/workflow/runner.clj"
                       "components/dag-executor/src/ai/miniforge/dag_executor/protocols/impl/docker.clj"]}

 :spec/constraints
 ["Only applies to governed mode with Docker executor"
  "Default network policy is :deny-all (already the case)"
  "Per-endpoint network allow-listing is deferred — support :deny-all and :allow-all only"
  "Secret values must never appear in logs, error messages, or evidence"
  "Use existing -e flag mechanism for env-scoped secrets"
  "Existing tests must pass"]

 :spec/acceptance-criteria
 [":runtime-spec from workflow config flows to Docker executor"
  ":network-policy :deny-all applies --network=none (existing behavior, now explicit)"
  ":network-policy :allow-all removes --network=none"
  "Secrets with :scope :env are injected as container env vars"
  "Secret names (not values) are logged at debug level"
  "Local mode ignores runtime-spec (no capsule to configure)"]

 :workflow/type :canonical-sdlc}
